BASIC DOCKER COMMANDS:

1. For getting the client and server versions

syntax: docker version


2. To know the version of docker installed

syntax: docker -v 


3. To view the system wide information like OS, Kernel and docker versions etc.

synatx: docker info


4. To download docker Images of a particular version(optional)

syntax: docker pull <Name-of-Image>: version


5. To get information about any other Docker command

syntax: docker --help


6. To search for an image in registry

synatx: docekr search <Name-of-Image>


7. To list all downloaded docker container images 

syntax: docekr images

8. For launching docker container 

syntax: docker run -it  <Name-of-Image> 

9. For listing all the running containers

syntax: docker ps


10. To start, stop, restart, kill the containers

syntax: docker start(or stop or restart or kill) <Name-of-Image>


11. To delete/remove a container

syntax: docker rm <Name-of-Container>


12. to delete/remove an image

syntax: docker rmi <Name-of-Image>


13. To display the history of socker image

syntax: docker history <Name-of-Image>


14. To display cpu, memory, and network I/O usage of all containers

syntax: docker stats


15. To build an image from a dockerfile

syntax: docker build -t[username/]<image-name>[:tag]<dockerfile-path>


16. To attach to a running container

syntax: docket attach docker <Name-of-Image>


17. To execute a new process in an existing container

syntax: docker exec -it <container-name><process>


18. To push an image to a registry

syntax: docker push [registry/][username/]<image-name><:tag>







